actions.text: Referred to House Committee on Post Office and Civil Service.
House Committee on Post Office and Civil Service Discharged by Unanimous Consent.
Called up by House by Unanimous Consent.
Received in the Senate. Read the second time. Placed on Senate Legislative Calendar under General Orders. Calendar No. 722.
Passed Senate without amendment and with a preamble by Voice Vote.

committees.committee: House Post Office and Civil Service

official_title: A joint resolution to authorize the designation of a calendar week in 1986 and each year thereafter as National Infection Control Week.

summary.text: (Measure passed House, amended) Authorizes and requests the President to designate a calendar week in 1986 and 1987 as National Infection Control Week.

titles.title: A joint resolution to authorize the designation of a calendar week in 1986 and each year thereafter as National Infection Control Week.
